If the same weather conditions apply, then 10 hours should be enough time for drying seven pairs of socks as well. The drying process depends on several factors such as air temperature, humidity, and wind speed; however, assuming these factors remain constant, we can estimate that it would take 10 hours to dry the seven pairs of socks.

Tom will need to wait 10 more hours for the seven pairs of socks to dry before bringing them back inside.
